#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.bitwise_xor.rst:2
msgid "maxframe.tensor.bitwise\\_xor"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:1 of
msgid "Compute the bit-wise XOR of two arrays element-wise."
msgstr "逐元素计算两个数组的按位异或。"

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:3 of
msgid ""
"Computes the bit-wise XOR of the underlying binary representation of the "
"integers in the input arrays. This ufunc implements the C/Python operator"
" ``^``."
msgstr ""
"计算输入数组中整数的二进制表示的按位异或。此 ufunc 实现了 C/Python 运算符"
" ``^``。"

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor of
msgid "参数"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:7
#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:9 of
msgid "Only integer and boolean types are handled."
msgstr "仅处理整数和布尔类型。"

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:11 of
msgid ""
"A location into which the result is stored. If provided, it must have a "
"shape that the inputs broadcast to. If not provided or `None`, a freshly-"
"allocated tensor is returned. A tuple (possible only as a keyword "
"argument) must have length equal to the number of outputs."
msgstr ""
"存储结果的位置。如果提供，其形状必须可以广播到输入形状。如果未提供或为 `"
"None`，则返回一个新分配的 tensor。元组（只能作为关键字参数）的长度必须"
"等于输出的数量。"

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:16 of
msgid ""
"Values of True indicate to calculate the ufunc at that position, values "
"of False indicate to leave the value in the output alone."
msgstr "值为 True 表示在该位置计算 ufunc，值为 False 表示保留输出中的值不变。"

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor of
msgid "返回"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:21 of
msgid "**out** -- Result."
msgstr "**out** -- 结果。"

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor of
msgid "返回类型"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:26 of
msgid ":py:obj:`logical_xor`, :py:obj:`bitwise_and`, :py:obj:`bitwise_or`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:28 of
msgid ":py:obj:`binary_repr`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:29 of
msgid "Return the binary representation of the input number as a string."
msgstr "以字符串形式返回输入数字的二进制表示。"

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:32 of
msgid "示例"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.arithmetic.bitxor.bitxor:33 of
msgid ""
"The number 13 is represented by ``00001101``. Likewise, 17 is represented"
" by ``00010001``.  The bit-wise XOR of 13 and 17 is therefore "
"``00011100``, or 28:"
msgstr ""
"数字 13 的二进制表示为 ``00001101``。同样，17 的二进制表示为 ``00010001``"
"。因此，13 和 17 的按位异或为 ``00011100``，即 28："

